A trained virologist can distinguish several types of cytopathic effects, even in unstained, living cultures (Plate 3-2
, Table 3-1
). Fixation and staining of the cell monolayer reveals further diagnostic details, notably inclusion bodies (Plate 6-1, Fig. 6-1) and syncytia (Plate 3-2c). These morphological consequences of viral infection are discussed in Chapter 6.
